Nigerian based American radio personality Daniel Foster is dead, his death has been linked to COVID-19. Foster who was born in Washington.D.C returned to Nigeria. He worked in the US at the Cathy Hughes Radio One and Mix 106.5. He started in Nigeria in the year 2000 at Cool F.M before going on to Inspiration F.M. He also joined City F.M in 2014 and last worked with Classic F.M. Foster worked as a judge on Idols West Africa alongside Dede Mabiaku and Nigeria Got Talent with Kate Henshaw. Dan Foster is survived by his wife Lovina Foster nee Okpara and three children.